132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 400
H.P. 254 House of Representatives, February 4, 2025
Resolve, Directing the Department of Public Safety, Office of the
State Fire Marshal to Compile a Statewide Inventory of Aqueous
Film-forming Foam Concentrate
Reference to the Committee on Environment and Natural Resources suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative ANKELES of Brunswick.
Cosponsored by President DAUGHTRY of Cumberland and
Representatives: ARFORD of Brunswick, BELL of Yarmouth, BRIDGEO of Augusta,
DOUDERA of Camden, GRAMLICH of Old Orchard Beach, OSHER of Orono, SOBOLESKI
of Phillips, Senator: TEPLER of Sagadahoc.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Aqueous film-forming foam concentrate inventory. Resolved: That
2 the Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal, referred to in this resolve
3 as "the office," shall initiate 2 programs to compile an inventory of aqueous film-forming
4 foam concentrate in the State as described under this section.
5 1. Beginning July 1, 2026, the office shall initiate a one-year program to collect
6 information regarding aqueous film-forming foam concentrate possessed by any public
7 entity in the State in an amount of 5 gallons or more. A public entity in the State shall
8 respond to a request for information from the office under this section within the timeline
9 determined by the office. For purposes of this section, "public entity" has the same meaning
10 as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 38, section 1272, subsection 17. The office
11 is authorized to continue to collect data from public entities after the end of the one-year
12 program until the submission of the inventory under section 3.
13 2. Beginning July 1, 2026, the office shall initiate a 2-year program to solicit
14 information from private entities in the State possessing aqueous film-forming foam
15 concentrate in an amount of 5 gallons or more.
16 Sec. 2. Inventory as public record. Resolved: That the inventory under section
17 1 is a public record as defined in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 1, section 402,
18 subsection 3.
19 Sec. 3. Report to Legislature. Resolved: That, no later than July 1, 2028, the
20 office shall submit the inventory under section 1 to the joint standing committees of the
21 Legislature having jurisdiction over environment and natural resources matters and
22 criminal justice and public safety matters.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This resolve directs the Department of Public Safety, Office of the State Fire Marshal,
2255 beginning July 1, 2026, to compile an inventory of aqueous film-forming foam concentrate
2266 possessed by any public entity in the State in an amount of 5 gallons or more and to solicit
2277 similar information from private entities.
28 The inventory is a public record, and the office is directed to submit the inventory to
29 the joint standing committees of the Legislature having jurisdiction over environment and
30 natural resources matters and criminal justice and public safety matters no later than July
31 1, 2028.
